>\ud83d\udcda</g-emoji> Documentation</h2>\n<p>The weights are ignored with reduction = \"elementwise_mean\" - this is actually what the documentation says but it would be much clearer to provide either:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>a warning that the weight are being ignored with \"elementwise_mean\" and suggest the use of reduction = \"sum\"</li>\n<li>or provide a reduction=\"mean\" which result in the weigths being used in a weighed mean. I guess this is the behaviour that most users would expect</li>\n</ul>", "body_text": "\ud83d\udcda Documentation\nThe weights are ignored with reduction = \"elementwise_mean\" - this is actually what the documentation says but it would be much clearer to provide either:\n\na warning that the weight are being ignored with \"elementwise_mean\" and suggest the use of reduction = \"sum\"\nor provide a reduction=\"mean\" which result in the weigths being used in a weighed mean. I guess this is the behaviour that most users would expect", "body": "## \ud83d\udcda Documentation\r\nThe weights are ignored with reduction = \"elementwise_mean\" - this is actually what the documentation says but it would be much clearer to provide either:\r\n\r\n- a warning that the weight are being ignored with \"elementwise_mean\" and suggest the use of reduction = \"sum\"\r\n- or provide a reduction=\"mean\" which result in the weigths being used in a weighed mean. I guess this is the behaviour that most users would expect"}